          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Puerto Rico Medicare Part B Equity Act of 2015</b></p> <p>Amends title XVIII (Medicare) of the Social Security Act to repeal the exclusion of residents of Puerto Rico from deemed enrollment under part B (Supplementary Medical Insurance Benefits) and thus apply it to them.</p> <p>Directs the Secretary of Health and Human Services to provide for a special seven-month enrollment period for such residents.</p> <p>Requires recalculation of the late enrollment penalty to 15% of the usual penalty for residents of Puerto Rico who are current enrollees or who enroll during a specified transition period.</p>]]></text>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
